label("$B$",dir(120),dir(120));
label("$C$",dir(180),dir(180));
draw(anglemark(dir(60)+dir(180),dir(60),dir(0),3));
[/asy]

Drawing a figure allows us to see that $3=AF=\frac{AE}{2}=\frac{AD}{4}=\frac{AC}{8}=\frac{AB}{16}\implies AB=\boxed{48}$.

